
Deus, qui inter cétera poténtiæ tuæ mirácula étiam in sexu frágili victóriam martýrii contulísti: concéde propítius; ut qui beátæ <sr>N.</s> Vírginis et Mártyris tuæ natalícia cólimus, per ejus ad te exémpla gradiámur. Per Dóminum.
O God, who, among the other wondrous works of thy power, hast bestowed the victory of martyrdom even on the weaker sex; mercifully grant that we who celebrate the heavenly birthday of blessed <sr>N.</s> thy Virgin and Martyr, may, by following her example, advance in the way that leadeth unto thee. Through our Lord.
